The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Shringar price band at Rs 47-53

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, March 22: Shringar Cinemas Ltd has fixed a price band of Rs 47-53 per share for its proposed initial public offering (IPO), the proceeds from which will finance its expansion plans.

 The IPO of the film exhibition and distribution company, which also operates a chain of multiplexes, will open on April 5 and close on April 11. Of the 81.50 lakh shares put up for sale, 2.50 lakh are reserved for allotment to employees. Of the balance, close to 39.50 lakh shares are reserved for allocation to qualified institutional buyers (QIBs) on a discretionary basis, 19.75 lakh are set aside for non-institutional bidders and 19.75 lakh for retail investors, both on a proportionate basis.

 The book-running lead managers to the issue are Enam Financial Consultants Pvt Ltd and JM Morgan Stanley Pvt Ltd.

 Shringar is betting on the optimistic forecast for the entertainment industry. According to a Ficci and Ernst amp; Young report, movies directly contributed Rs 4,500 crore in the Rs 19,20-crore entertainment business during 2003. 




